I have no idea if it is normal or not. My thoughts on this subject are 1.
Why did you marry if you still carried a flame for this other man? 2. So you
love your husband? There are all kinds of love. Best friend. Trustworthy.
These are fantastic traits, but they don't necessarily mean husband and wife
love.

I am concerned about marriage doubts one month into the marriage. Did you
have these doubts before you got married? If not, why do they crop up now?
If yes, what made you decide to proceed?

These are tough questions, and I don't need the answers to them. But I think
you do. In my opinion, you need to

1. Cut out contact with the other &quot;friend&quot; until your feelings on this
matter are clear.
2. Get thyself into counseling to work out the aforementioned questions or
the ones a skilled professional (which I am not btw) gives you to help you
sort out how you got here and where you go from here.
3. Use very reliable birth control very reliably. Now is not the time to add
a child to the mix. All decisions get more difficult when a child is
involved.

Best of luck!
