Who knows why you're having those thoughts.  The important thing here
is that if you do love your DH, then break off all contact with your
X.  To feel the way you do about him, and apparently him about you, is
not a friendship, even if you do currently keep your contact with him
friendly.

Break it off.  If you can do that, then you'll know that you truly do
love your husband.  If you can't, then it may be that you're really in
love with the other man, and your DH is really only your friend.  But
whatever you decide, do it openly and honestly.  If you're having
contact with the other guy, or you ever will have contact with him,
and you can't tell you DH the truth about having the contact, and the
full nature of the contact, then you're cheating.  Moreover, all this
contact with the OG, however innocent, will simply get in the way of
your relationship with your DH.

You're still at a cross-roads you should've chosen long ago.  Decide
which way it's going to be, choose a road, and then stay only on that
road.

