I'm going to say something which sounds condescending, but isn't meant
to be.  &quot;Grow up!&quot;

What I mean is that something all of us have to face is that the world
is full of interesting attractive people.

One approach to life is to have as many relationships with as many of
these people as one can.  There is nothing wrong with this approach,
and many people spend some of their life in this mode - some people
spend all their life in this mode.

Another approach (and this is the one people who are getting married
are usually taking) is to say:  &quot;OK, I've chosen this good person whom
I love to build a lifetime relationship with.  That doesn't mean I
won't ever meet other people who excite me, but it does mean that my
desire to build a life with my spouse is more important than the
excitement of being with other people.&quot;

So choose, and commit.  If you are in the first mode, get divorced,
and stay unmarried until you feel firmly in the second mode.  If you
are in the second mode,  be committed about it, not half-hearted.
