I was thinking that this might be a perfect example of what I was
talking about on the Confession thread: that cheating can have at its
roots a fear of intimacy, which is why the most common times for
infidelity to occur include birth of a child, death of a family
member, cross-country move, retirement..... and immediately before or
after the wedding!!!

The ink is barely dry on the wedding certificate, which makes it all
reality. Reality of an intimate, one-on-one relationship can be scary.
So what the OP is doing is inserting a third party into that
relationship, to make it a more comfortable triangle. Even if she
doesn't actually cheat or conduct an affair, having her emotions and
feelings for this man is enough to make him the third point. As she
allows her mind to fly into fantasy and wondering about &quot;what if&quot; she
is effectively turning away from her new husband and placing distance
between them.

