in your choice, and still find yourself suddenly terrified at the
reality of committing forever! Maybe that's just me though. And, I
think it's very common  to be scared of intimacy, so it doesn't mean
there's necessarily anything wrong with the OP.

Damaging to the marriage? Yes - if you believe that the whole idea of
marriage is to become increasingly intimate with your spouse, and
that's the sort of relationship you were hoping for.

